Main_Caption:
Составлена пятерка лучших автомобилей ко Дню влюбленных. Эксперты отмечают, что разным стадиям отношений больше подходят разные авто. Так, в начале отношений кататься парам лучше на Mazda MX-5. Родстер подойдет для свиданий в городе и для небольших путешествий. Правда наиболее романтичным в России оно будет в летнее время, когда можно воспользоваться всеми прелестями открытого верха.

Для пар, которые вступили в более серьезную и близкую фазу общения советуют Fiat 500 от ателье Garage Italia Custom. "Эротическая" новинка украшена рисунками из Камасутры, на окнах предусмотрены шторки, а в список оснащения включены наручники и плетка.

Тем, кто уже планирует дальнейшие серьезные шаги и намерен прожить "горе и радости, болезни и здравии" со своим партнером рекомендуется рассмотреть Mercedes-Benz E-Class L. Версия Maybach имеет кожаный салон, а увеличенная колесная база значительно расширяет пространство на заднем ряду сидений.

Если пера уже планирует завести детей, то выбрать можно Chrysler Pacifica. Минивэн с мощным двигателем подойдет любой семье.

Если влюбленные любят путешествия, то на вооружение следует взять автодом на базе Volkswagen California XXL на базе Crafter. Для максимального комфорта в любом месте комплектация включает кровать, душ, кухню и выдвижную крышу.

Main_Caption: Massive thanks to @mdnovaman for hand turning me yet another set of #subaru #injector #tophats for the #1jzrx8 I had these on my #mx5 #turbo build a few years ago and they worked faultlessly! I've used them on at least 3 other builds I've done. From a sketch in his head to this finished product - superb👌
List_Of_Comments: ["@mdnovaman  Truer words never before been spoken. The Subaru injectors are useless for Subaru cars that are being tuned but large enough for smaller engine cars looking for boost. Or indeed having another 2 added to make them useable In a 6 pot means you don't have to go 1000cc or 750 etc like you would on a 4 banger", 'I’ve had this set up ✌️👌', 'I worked out the other day I’ve now made sets of these for around 7 cars. All various states of tune and with them now fitting the 1jz engines. And I’m making another batch of sets to fit an rb20 and 350z too. Injectors can be one of the big outlays when doing a NA-T conversion on a lot of cars as most are using scrap yard parts for budget boost. With reasonable sized injectors available from factory cars. These can be had and fitted for a tenth of the price and with OEM reliability using the top hats.', 'It works so well']

Harddog M2 Hard Core fits nicely.
Fairly straightforward install takes about 7-8hrs. Be prepared to trim sheet metal in tight quarters. Rear glass window barely fits between bars, 1/8" more room woulda been perfect. 
So... tall drivers, im 6'1" area, your head will rest on the bar when you lean all the way back, I would  recommend considering ordering the foam covers. Im going to make some custom ones.
Also, it will affect your seat position. My "optimal" setting is slid forward 2 clicks and leaned all the way back. With the bar the seat doesnt go quite all the way back but its doable for me. Like I say, safety before lesser concerns (but after tacos)

Turbos are more efficient noise reducers at low rpm and make way cooler noises on boost', 'Super charger 3k + megasquirt or turbo 1k + megasquirt', '@neckbreakersmedia which kits are you referring to? fm? eBay?', 'I got a93 1.6 and I just scooped up a Jackson racing for a deal because everyone else is doing turbo', 'Suupperre charger!!!!!!!! Keep the low end and still go fast. Plus easier to install and more reliable. The rotrex kit is baller', '@mrgarard are you currently running with MS or did you stretch the MAF over to your current intake setup?', 'Track Dog Racing Rotrex or Kraftwerks', 'Diy. The kits out there are garbage.', 'Both. Compound charge that shit (:', "@skychichis thanks man! yeah this header is a bit bigger than stock. 4-2-1 flows pretty nice. quality isn't the best, welds suck, but can't beat the price!", 'DC- AC inverter plus Black n Decker 1hp leaf blower', 'Procharger', 'If you need more info pm me on both let me know I have the list of pros and cons', "Turbo. Period. Get a small turbo that spools quick and you'll make more torque than a blower. Piece together a kit and it will be cheaper/make more power than a supercharger. Dm I've gone through the whole thing lol", 'Superchager 🤘', '@sidewayseightsix on my way to home depot 😅', 'Go for a kraftwerks or jackson racing supercharger', '@le_bleu88 was looking into both of those kits. not sure the cost of the TDR kit tho, doesnt say on their site. sent them an email tho. kraftwerks is about 4k 😥', 'Clean Miata!', '@yinooo exactly my thoughts', '@le_bleu88 k20 swap, nice! I looked into that before too 😅 that will be sweet dude.', 'Rotrex, mspnp.  As much as I liked a t25 on my 1.6, having something below 4500rpm would have been nice.', '@mrgarard is that the stock headers with heat wrap?', '@mrgarard appreciate it. Never took the heat sheild off so i was curious cause that looks way better haha. Clean ride man.', '@patrick_hewitt i extended the wiring', "More power easier out of a turbo but more reliable with a supercharger. No lines running around like a rats nest making it look really untidy.', "@mrgarard Ohhh You Have A 1.8 right ? They can get pricey but for what it's worth if you're not worried about HP supercharger is the way to go with the reliability in mind not saying turbo can't do it either but right now I'm in the process of buying a k20z3 longblock and put in the miata. I'll stay n.a for awhile until i do a rotrex setup", '@skychichis obx + heat wrap', "@phoyndanielle that's why im leaning toward a supercharger", '@mrgarard just most of them in general.
